resses the specific environmental issues of pollution, ecosystem management, and climate change. Chapters include summaries of key concepts and discussion questions, as well as informative ";spotlights"; offering brief overviews of topics. With a highly accessible structure and useful illustrative features, A Guide to EU Environmental Law provides a long-overdue synthetic resource on EU environmental law for students and for anyone working in environmental policy or environmental science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEnvironmental lawzEuropean Union countries. 0aEnvironmental policyzEuropean Union countries. 7aLAW / Environmental.2bisacsh1 aRowell, Arden, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishz978311070486008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020z9783110704587oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520968059zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968059423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520968059.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070486-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020